But the exemptions are many.
&nbsp;
<h2> Who can not pay it
In fact, the entrance fee will be required only for non-resident daily tourists in Veneto who do not stay in hotels, guest rooms and B&amp;B in the city (who already pay the tourist tax) and will have an amount of 5 euros per person. Exempted from the payment who will go to Venice from 16 to 8.30 in the morning or who will visit the smaller islands, as well as the minors of 14 years, disabled and relative companions. Derogues are also provided for spouses, cohabitants and relatives of the residents of Veneto up to the third degree and also for those who, without parental ties, visit residents and domiciled in the city or in the smaller islands, for workers and workers (employees or self-employed), for students and students of any degree and order of schools and universities which are based in the ancient city or in the smaller islands and all the members of Venice.
&nbsp;
<h2> How to pay
Payment will take place through the online platform (http://cda.ve.it) where you can get a QR Code to be exhibited in case of controls but it will also be possible to buy a coupon in the tobacco shops of all Italy.
&nbsp;
<h2> What is the risk
The fine for those who were found not in order with the ticket goes from 50 euros to 300 euros. Instead, a criminal complaint is found to be found to declare the false to obtain the exemption.&nbsp;

